deck: Dr. Linda McGill was a scientist for an aerodynamics company. She met and fell in love with Ben Grimm who was a test pilot for the company.
description:
Fantastic Four (2005 Movie)

Debbie McIlvane was a loose interpretation of Dr. Linda McGill and was played by Laurie Holden. When Ben returned from space and transformed into the Thing, he took it upon himself to break the news to his fiancee. Ben arrives in NYC and calls Debbie from their apartment. Debbie notices a shadowy figure in a nearby phone booth when she speaks to Ben and rushes outside. Ben felt reluctant to reveal himself but when he did, Debbie was horrified and ran into the apartment.

Debbie appeared one last time when Ben and the rest of the Fantastic Four saved a bunch of people from a chain of accidents on the FDR Bridge. As everybody cheered for the Fantastic Four, Debbie approached Ben but she refused to let him embrace her. Debbie takes off her engagement ring, places it near Ben's feet and leaves him heartbroken.
name: Dr. Linda McGill

deck: From Bad Girl to Heroine
description:
Origin

Su Shan was the main assistant of Dr. Sinn, a world be world conqueror. Eventually betrayed and pushed out of a plane by Dr. Sinn when his schemes start to unravel due to the interference of Jet Powers she is rescued by Powers from falling to her death and taken to his hidden mesa laboratory. There she takes a compound that erases her memory, which is later restored by Jet Powers.

Despite this she still tries to kill Powers and later escapes from him, rejoining Dr. Sinn he later once again tries to kill her and is once again saved by Jet Powers. This time she rethinks her relationship with the two and teams up with Jet saving him from a death trap Dr. Sinn has placed him in, after that they become an item with Su Shan returning to Jet’s mesa headquarters.
name: Su Shan

deck: The owner and founder of the Westman Construction Company.
description: Sam Westman is the owner and founder of the Westman Construction Company something he built from nothing after his wife died. He created the company to support his son Jerry Westman but soon was more occupied with the company than with spending time with his son. Eventually the two were at odds when his company was hired to demolish a park in favor of some factories. The construction was halted by a group of teenage protesters and Namor the Sub-Mariner who helped change Sam's mind.
name: Sam Westman

deck: The son of Sam Westman founder of the Westman Construction Company.
description:
Jerry along with Barb, Joey, and a number of other teenagers protested the building of a factory where a park was already in place. This put Jerry at odds with his father Sam Westman who is the owner of Westman Construction Company and was hired to level the park and build the industrial complex that would replace it.

Namor the Sub-Mariner decided to stand with the young protesters after a couple of employees turned to violence. The protesters reminded him that damage to their environment also effects the oceans so that it'd be wise to help them get some awareness by showing up and one of their meetings. Not only did Namor show up in support Sam Westman did as well, only he was there to attack the Sub-Mariner in his demolition machine dubbed Brutivac. Just when Sam had the mighty Sub-Mariner in a position of vulnerability and tried to run him down Jerry stepped in the way only to get struck by the Brutivac instead. The impact caused Sam to snap out of his moment of madness and allowed him to reflect on all he's done. Jerry ended up being alright so he and his father thanked Namor and decided it best to stop working so hard and to spend some time together instead.
name: Jerry Westman

deck: He found the secrets of chemical compound able to combine the power of a beast with the mind of man.
description:
Dr. Vryolak discovered a labyrinth in Aegean with a secret formula that was able to combine the strength of an animal with the mind of a man. He would later use this concoction on his own son who was losing a battle with a disease that would soon take his life. Having already lost his wife he would not let his son die as well. Upon giving Miklos the treatment he began to grow stronger eventually changing into a fabled Minotaur of legend.

When Whitney Frost washed up on shore Dr. Vryolak decided to nurse her back to health and mislead her into thinking he could fix her face. In actuality he wanted to create another beast using the chemistry he used on his son to create a mate for him. Thankfully with the combined efforts of Iron Man, Jasper Sitwell and even Miklos himself that didn't happen. Miklos sacrificed himself to save the others while he and his father stayed in a cavern as the entire island collapsed on top of them seemingly killing them both.
name: Dr. Vryolak
